'''Dorney Road Landfill''' is a [[Superfund]] site in [[Mertztown, Pennsylvania]].<ref name="epa">{{cite web
|title=''Mid-Atlantic Superfund: Dorney Road Landfill''
|author=[[United States Environmental Protection Agency|Environmental Protection Agency]]
|url=http://www.epa.gov/reg3hwmd/npl/PAD980508832.htm
}}</ref>

==History==
Formerly an [[Open-pit mining|open-pit mine]], this site housed a [[landfill]] from 1952 to 1978. During that time, the disposal of toxic materials caused contamination of local [[groundwater]]. Dorney Road Landfill was added to the [[National Priorities List]] in 1984.<ref name="epa" />

