'''Mictomagnetism''' is a spin system in which various [[exchange interactions]] are mixed. It is observed in several kinds of [[alloys]], including Cu-Mn, Fe-Al and Ni-Mn alloys. Cooled in zero magnetic field, these materials have low [[remanence]] and [[coercivity]]. Cooled in a magnetic field, they have much larger remanence and the [[hysteresis loop]] is shifted in the direction opposite to the field (an effect similar to [[exchange bias]]).<ref>{{cite book  |last = Chikazumi |first = Sōshin |title = Physics of Ferromagnetism |publisher = [[Clarendon Press]] |date = 1997 |isbn = 0-19-851776-9}}</ref>

